id: pm-0z7n
title: "Alias shim layer: config-aware hidden aliases with one-line migration hints (foundation for all consolidations)"
description: "Build the shared mechanism every consolidation cluster uses: a declarative alias table mapping old spellings (e.g. list-open, start-task, history-repair) to new noun-verb invocations, hidden from help, emitting a single config-suppressible migration hint on stderr, with a spelling-parity spec asserting every aliased invocation produces byte-identical output to its canonical form. Duplicate check: no existing alias-shim or deprecation-layer item."
type: Feature
status: open
priority: 1
tags[4]: agent-ux,"area:cli","area:contracts",simplification
created_at: "2026-07-05T04:53:04.314Z"
updated_at: "2026-07-11T16:23:32.226Z"
author: maintainer-agent
estimated_minutes: 240
acceptance_criteria: "Declarative alias table drives Commander registration; aliases hidden from default help but resolvable; migration hint printed once per invocation to stderr, suppressible via config key; spelling-parity spec proves alias output identical to canonical; contracts/completions expose canonical forms and mark aliases deprecated"
parent: pm-n7rr
risk: medium
confidence: high
